```python
import numpy as np, matplotlib.pyplot as plt, librosa as lr
from IPython.display import Audio
```

# STFT


```python
sr = 44100
length = 1
freq1, freq2 = 60, 700
t = np.linspace(0, length, sr * length)

y = np.concatenate([
    np.sin(2 * np.pi * t[:int(sr * length / 4)] * freq1),
    np.sin(2 * np.pi * t[int(sr * length / 4):] * freq2),
])

plt.plot(y)
plt.show()

display(Audio(y, rate=sr))
```

```python
stft = lr.stft(y=y, n_fft=2048, window='hann')

print(stft.shape)
# librosa nimmt automatisch nur die haelfte der f-coef bis nyquist 

plt.subplot(2, 1, 1)
plt.plot(np.abs(stft[:, 10]))
plt.subplot(2, 1, 2)
plt.plot(np.abs(stft[:, 40]))
plt.show()
```
